# Testing Standards

## Framework & Location
- Framework: Vitest
- Location: `chrome-extension/src/**/__tests__/` with `*.test.ts` naming
- Run all: `pnpm -F chrome-extension test`
- Run targeted: `pnpm -F chrome-extension test -- -t "test name"`

## What to Test
- Business logic in `agent/` — message construction, provider selection, token counting, action parsing
- Utility functions in `utils.ts`, `messages/utils.ts`, `messages/service.ts`
- Schema validation in `packages/schema-utils/`
- Do NOT write tests for React UI components unless they contain logic

## Mocking
- Mock Chrome APIs (`chrome.storage`, `chrome.tabs`, `chrome.debugger`) — they don't exist in Vitest
- Mock network calls (`fetch`, AI SDK `generateObject`/`generateText`) — tests must be deterministic and offline
- Use `vi.mock()` at the module level, not inside test bodies
- Prefer minimal mocks that test actual logic paths, not just mock call counts

## Test Quality
- Each test must have a clear failure message explaining what broke and why
- Prefer testing behavior (what the function returns/throws) over implementation (which internal function was called)
- When an agent bug is fixed, add a regression test to prevent recurrence
- Tests that hit real LLM APIs are not unit tests — put them in `e2e/` only

## Vitest Config Notes
- The Vitest config lives in `chrome-extension/vite.config.mts`
- Workspace packages (`@extension/dev-utils`, `@extension/hmr`) must be built before tests run; if you see "failed to resolve entry", run `pnpm ready` in the relevant package first
